The Economic Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) has confirmed it took into custody the former Attorney General and Minister of Justice, Mohammed Bello Adoke as he arrived Nnamdi Azikwe International Airport, Abuja on Thursday. Adoke arrived the country (Nigeria) from Dubai, United Arab Emirates around 3;45 pm accompanied… December 19, 2019 In "News" Abuja— The trial of former Justice Minister, Mohammed Adoke, over his role in the $1.3 billion Malabu Oil scandal may begin any moment from now, following his arrival in Nigeria yesterday. December 20, 2019 In "News" ABUJA—A High Court of the Federal Capital Territory sitting at Jabi, has issued a bench warrant for the arrest of the immediate past Attorney General of the Federation, Mohammed Adoke, SAN, former Minister of Petroleum, Dan Etete, and four other persons that were fingered in the $1.2billion Malabu Oil bloc… April 18, 2019 In "News"